1
00:00:04,733 --> 00:00:06,806
They used to have
this expression,

2
00:00:06,806 --> 00:00:10,260
“What do you give the man
who has everything?”

3
00:00:10,260 --> 00:00:12,805
Your heart.

4
00:00:12,805 --> 00:00:14,346
Love and devotion.

5
00:00:14,346 --> 00:00:17,523
[Give Heart Get Heart]

6
00:00:17,523 --> 00:00:20,801
And Guru Mahārāj said,
“Offer with love and devotion,

7
00:00:20,801 --> 00:00:22,802
He’ll accept with
love and devotion.”

8
00:00:22,802 --> 00:00:26,114
Guru Mahārāj says,
“Give heart and receive heart.”

9
00:00:26,114 --> 00:00:29,820
That’s the most wonderful thing
about Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

10
00:00:29,820 --> 00:00:32,775
Not anticipating something else.

11
00:00:32,775 --> 00:00:35,063
Give heart, receive heart.

12
00:00:35,063 --> 00:00:39,315
To know that Kṛṣṇa could actually
care about us, is inconceivable.

13
00:00:40,102 --> 00:00:46,557
His coin, Kṛṣṇa,
His way of reciprocating is heart.

14
00:00:46,557 --> 00:00:48,957
Other things are given … 
what is it?

15
00:00:48,957 --> 00:00:53,617
“Muktiṁ dadāti karhichit
sma na bhakti-yogam” (SB: 5.6.18).

16
00:00:53,617 --> 00:00:58,276
He may give mukti easily,
but not bhakti.

17
00:00:58,276 --> 00:01:03,074
Because bhakti … “Ahaḿ bhakta-parādhīno
hy asvatantra iva dvija” (SB: 9.4.63);

18
00:01:03,074 --> 00:01:06,028
it’s as if He loses
His Independence,

19
00:01:06,028 --> 00:01:09,767
and He comes under the control
of that devotee.

20
00:01:09,767 --> 00:01:15,784
That’s Kṛṣṇa conception,
a unique aspect of Kṛṣṇa conception.

